------------------------------------------------------------
a. Main Function 


START

IF argc is not equal to 2
	PRINT usage message
	EXIT_FAILURE

OPEN file with READ_ONLY access
	IF it fails
		PRINT error message
		EXIT_FAILURE

Initialise GLOBAL variable stack array ** set maximum stack to 100(?) **
Initialise top to -1 ** empty stack **

FOR all lines in the file:
	READ line
	IF line can't be read
		Error message
		EXIT_FAILURE
	Store contents of line in variable ** strip trailing spaces also**

	SWITCH across all possible functions
		IF variable matches with any function
			Call the function
		DEFAULT
			PRINT error message
			EXIT_FAILURE

Close the file
Display the stack
EXIT_SUCCESS

END


-------------------------------------------------------------
b. Implement push opcode

START

IF int passed is not an integer OR there is no argument
	PRINT error message
	EXIT_FAILURE

IF top IS EQUAL to MAX
	Overflow (not dealing with it for now)
	EXIT_SUCCESS

top++
stack[top] = int
RETURN (top)

END


--------------------------------------------------------------
c. Implement pall opcode

START

IF top IS EQUAL to -1
	RETURN

WHILE top IS NOT EQUAL TO -1
	PRINT stack[top]
	top--

RETURN

END
